PROGRAM 6

Launch EC2 Instances in Public and Private Subnets

Aim
To launch web server in public subnet and database server in private subnet.

Step 1 Open EC2

1. Search EC2.
2. Open EC2 dashboard.

Step 2 Launch Public EC2

1. Click Launch Instance.
2. Enter instance name.
3. Select Amazon Linux.
4. Select t2.micro.
5. Select public subnet.
6. Enable Auto Assign Public IP.
7. Create security group.
8. Allow HTTP and SSH.
9. Click Launch Instance.

Step 3 Install Apache Web Server
Connect using SSH.
Run commands
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install httpd -y
sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl enable httpd

Step 4 Launch Private EC2

1. Launch another instance.
2. Select private subnet.
3. Disable public IP.
4. Configure database.

Result
Public and private EC2 instances launched successfully.
